tab.version_description: Capo'ed for open chords that ring out (matches sustained keyboard), well suited to acoustic covers, two different strumming variations defined.

wiki_tab.content:
Chords for strumming
--------------------
[ch]Cmaj7[/ch]  x3200x
[ch]D[/ch]      x0023x  (or play D/A as shown for bassier sound)
[ch]Bm7[/ch]    x2020x
[ch]B7[/ch]     x2420x
[ch]B[/ch]      x2444x

Capo 2nd fret (for no capo or piano chords, transpose +2)

versions.version_description: The chords I've written out sound best on capo 6, but you can definitely transpose them to get a lower or a higher sound. Keep in mind I found these chords out by ear.
This is a ukulele tab, chords aren't too easy. I only strum down once, so I don't have submitted a strumming pattern.

imo Cmaj7 sounds better in place of C :)
Strumming pattern: DD DUDU sounds nice
